[1] Digital COVID certificate
Date: Thu 3 Jun 2021
Source: Forbes [edited]
https://www.forbes.com/sites/suzannerowankelleher/2021/06/03/the-eus-digital-covid-certificate-could-soon-be-available-to-americans/?sh=abe6c07a2a65


On Tuesday [1 Jun 2021], the European Commission announced that the European Union [EU] Digital COVID Certificate was finally live. At launch, 7 EU countries are using the app, and the other bloc countries will roll it out by 1 Jul [2021]. The free mobile app provides digital proof via a QR code that a traveler has been vaccinated against COVID-19, has recently tested negative for COVID-19, or has recovered from the illness.

A European Union spokesperson told CNN [Cable News Network] yesterday [Wed 2 Jun 2021] that the app could be extended to citizens from non-EU countries, including the United States. In principle, holders of the EU Digital COVID Certificate should be exempted from travel restrictions such as quarantine requirements.

"Right now, if you're an American, not living in the EU, you could get the certificate if you ask the national authorities of a member state to give you that certificate based on some proof that you've been vaccinated, or had a recent COVID test," said the EU spokesperson. The decision on whether to allow non-EU citizens to use the app would rest with each individual member state.

The Digital COVID Certificate just started rolling out. Each EU member state can launch the certificate on a voluntary basis provided it is ready to issue and verify certificates and have the necessary legal base in place. The commission is calling the month of June [2021] the "warm-up phase." So far, only 7 European member countries are using the pass: Bulgaria, Croatia, Czechia, Denmark, Germany, Greece, and Poland.

Sixteen other EU countries plus Switzerland have finished the testing phase and are technically ready to begin using the pass at any time. These include Austria, Belgium, Cyprus, Estonia, France, Ireland, Italy, Latvia, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, Netherlands, Portugal, Romania, Spain, Sweden, and Switzerland.

In addition, 7 more countries -- 4 in the EU and 3 outside the bloc -- are currently in the testing phase: Finland, Hungary, Iceland, Liechtenstein, Norway, Slovakia, and Slovenia. The EU Digital COVID Certificate includes limited information such as the traveler's name, date of birth, and relevant information about the vaccine received, COVID test results, or recovery from COVID. This data remains on the certificate and is not stored or retained by visited countries.

All 3 vaccines available in the United States -- Pfizer, Moderna, and Johnson & Johnson -- will be covered under the EU certificate. Last month [May 2021], the 27 ambassadors for European Union agreed to open their borders to vaccinated Americans and other non-EU citizens after more than a year of travel restrictions during the COVID-19 pandemic. Some EU member states, including Greece, had already started allowing tourists to visit without quarantine requirements if they have been vaccinated. Next week, Spain and France will open their borders to US travelers on 7 Jun and 9 Jun [2021], respectively.

[byline: Suzanne Rowan Kelleher]

