[5A] Bangladesh
Date: Fri 4 Jun 2021 03:11 a.m. BST
Source: The Daily Star [edited]
https://www.thedailystar.net/backpage/news/30-more-die-covid-1687-get-infected-2104617


As Bangladesh continues to fight against the pandemic with rising infections in frontier districts, it recorded 30 more deaths from COVID-19 in 24 hours as of yesterday morning [3 Jun 2021], raising the death toll to 12 724. In addition, health authorities reported 1687 new cases after testing 16 982 samples during the same period. With the new cases, the total caseload rose to 805 980, said a handout of the Directorate General of Health Services.

The daily infection rate rose to 9.94%, up from Wednesday's [2 Jun 2021] 9.81%, while the mortality rate remained static at 1.58%. The handout said 746 035 patients, including 1970 during the 24-hour period, have recovered so far.

Rajshahi division witnessed the highest number of 8 deaths during the 24 hours, while 6 patients died in each of Dhaka and Chattorgram divisions, 4 in Rangpur, 3 in Khulna, 2 in Sylhet, and one in Barishal division.

Bangladesh reported its first novel coronavirus cases on [8 Mar 2020] and the 1st death on [18 Mar 2020].

