[5B] India
Date: Fri 4 Jun 2021 06:26 IST
Source: The Times of India (TOI), Times News Network (TNN) [edited]
https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/70-of-1-3-lakh-fresh-cases-are-from-maharashtra-south-india/articleshow/83222555.cms


The 2nd wave of COVID-19 is steadily declining across the country, but the fall in cases has been much sharper in northern and central India than in the south and Maharashtra. India reported 131 739 fresh cases on [Thu 3 Jun 2021]. Nearly 70% of these cases were reported from Maharashtra and the southern region alone, which together accounted for 91 308 new cases, as per TOI's COVID database.

The share of Maharashtra and the south in total cases has been creeping up over the past month [May 2021]. On [27 May 2021], exactly a week ago, the share stood at 66.5%. In comparison, on [6 May 2021], the day India recorded its highest single-day case count of 414 554, Maharashtra and south together made up 50% of the total. A comparison of Thursday's [3 Jun 2021] case count with that of [6 May 2021] reveals while Maharashtra and the south have together seen a 56% decline in cases the national count has gone down by over 68%.

[byline: Amit Bhattacharya]

