[5C] Nepal
Date: Thu 3 Jun 2021 04:39 p.m. NPT
Source: The Himalayan Times [abridged, edited]
https://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/nepals-active-caseload-stands-at-101839-covid-death-toll-reaches-7630


Nepal on Thursday [3 Jun 2021] reported 5825 new cases of coronavirus infection from across the country. With this, the COVID-19 caseload has reached 576 936. The nationwide death toll has reached 7630 with 75 COVID-related fatalities reported today [3 Jun 2021].

Nepal's COVID-19 recovery rate climbed to 81% on Thursday [3 Jun 2021], as opposed to 80.8% on Wednesday [2 Jun 2021] and the total number of recoveries in the country as of today [3 Jun 2021] is 467 467.

As many as 5904 people who had earlier contracted the disease recovered in the past 24 hours. With fresh recoveries slightly more than the new infections of late, the active COVID-19 case count currently stands at 101 839. Meanwhile, antigen tests confirmed 1000 positive cases in the past 24 hours. As such, total infections from both the RT-PCR and antigen tests added up to 6825.

In the same time frame, 1630 infections were reported in the capital city while Lalitpur and Bhaktapur reported 298 and 129 cases, respectively. There are 831 individuals in various quarantine facilities across Nepal.

According to the health ministry, 21 773 total tests were conducted in the last 24 hours, of which 18 562 were PCR tests while 3211 were antigen tests. With this, a total of 3 106 938 PCR tests have been carried out in Nepal to date [3 Jun 2021].

On Wednesday [2 Jun 2021], Nepal's coronavirus case count reached 571 111 with 4524 newly confirmed cases.

