communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Data by country, area, or territory for 4 Jun 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20JUNE4_1622922177.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 44.3% of daily case numbers and 50.7% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 68.00 million cases. Brazil reported over 95 000 cases over the last 24 hours followed by Argentina with 35 017 cases, Colombia (27 000), and the USA (15 989). Twelve additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (Canada, Chile, Costa Rica, Guatemala, Mexico, Peru, Dominican Republic, Venezuela, Paraguay, Uruguay, Bolivia, and Cuba). Two additional countries (Panama and Honduras) reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 10.9% of daily case numbers and 11.1% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 54.52 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium (2 cases), Switzerland (4 cases), and Kazakhstan, among others. Twelve countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 3 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 6.2% of daily case numbers and 4.6% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 10.22 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (9657) over the last 24 hours, followed by Iraq, Pakistan, UAE, Bahrain, Tunisia, Afghanistan, Kuwait, Saudi Arabia, and Oman. Jordan and Egypt reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 2.2% of daily case numbers and 1.2% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.54 million cases. South Africa (5360) reported the highest number of cases over last 24 hours followed by Uganda (1083). Zambia and Namibia reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Botswana, Gabon, Rwanda, and Cameroon, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 4.5% of daily case numbers and 4.1% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.09 million cases. Malaysia reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 8200 cases), followed by Philippines, Japan, Mongolia, Cambodia, South Korea, and China.

- The South East Asia region reported 31.8% of the daily newly reported cases and 28.3% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 32.38 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 132 000 cases, followed by Nepal (5825), Indonesia (5353), Sri Lanka (3297), Thailand (2631), and Bangladesh (1687).

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 4 Jun 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

