[In the past 24 hours, 5 countries including India (121 476), Brazil (38 482), Argentina (30 950), Colombia (30 000), and the USA (17 271) have reported the highest numbers of cases, all reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours. A global total of 10 086 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (late 2 Jun 2021 to late 3 Jun 2021). A total of 47 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 14 of the 47 countries are from the European region, 13 are from the Americas region, 9 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 6 are from the South East Asia region, 3 are from the Western Pacific region, and 2 from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have decreased by 6.4%, while daily reported deaths have increased by 2.7%. Similar comparative 7-day averages in the USA show a 5.1% increase in daily reported cases and 17.6% increase in reported deaths.

Impression: The global daily reported over 450 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours with over 173.31 million cumulative reported cases and over 3.72 million reported deaths. - Mod.UBA]
